=====================================  .gitlab-ci.yml =======================
This is deployment repo root .gitlab-ci.yml and we used to trigger or call the drill pipeline from here only ..by going to build>pipeline>New pipeline and then provide

drill_tier variable like prod or preprod accordingly we use to get all the stages to click the buttons and perfomed and run the all the stages accordingly.


and above all the yamls is belongs from cicd-templates repos ...we have included all that yaml here in deployment repo.

include:
  # ── Use Case 1: App service deployment ──────────────────────────────────────
  # Default path — active whenever DRILL_TIER is NOT set.
  # Stages defined inside this template: publish · validate · deploy
  - project: 'itepaypg-sbiepay2/infra/devops/cicd-templates'
    ref: main
    file: 'templates/cd/deploy.single.yml'
    rules:
      - if: '$DRILL_TIER == null || $DRILL_TIER == ""'

  # ── Use Case 2: DC/DR Drill ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Active ONLY when operator sets DRILL_TIER in "Run pipeline" dialog.
  # Stages defined inside this template: Maintenance_Page · DC_Application_Services
  #                                       DR_Application_Services · MirrorMaker2
  # DRILL_TIER is NEVER set by any CI trigger — safe discriminator.
  - project: 'itepaypg-sbiepay2/infra/devops/cicd-templates'
    ref: main
    file: 'templates/cd/deploy.drill.yml'
    rules:
      - if: '$DRILL_TIER != null && $DRILL_TIER != ""'


